values.description:
[view here](http://gazebosim.org/tutorials?tut=drcsim_create_atlas_world&cat=drcsim&branch=create_atlas_world)

While reviewing [PR#143](#!/osrf/gazebo_tutorials/pull-request/143/update-to-modify-world/diff), I found the instructions clunky and potentially confusing. This new tutorial revamps the steps to teach users how to create a new world and spawn Atlas into it.

I'd like feedback to determine whether or not to delete the other tutorial, [drcsim_modify_world](http://gazebosim.org/tutorials?tut=drcsim_modify_world&cat=drcsim). I directly lifted a few lines from it, so this new tutorial can be thought of as a rewrite of the modify_world, suggesting to me that modify_world is no longer necessary.
values.title: New "Spawn Atlas into custom world" to replace "Modify environment" (DRCSim)
